Okay, I hung up the new nest box during the day. This is how it looks in the garden.
But let's take a moment to look back. "What's inside?" seems no one has asked.
The top is an ESP32 camera board with a fisheye lens camera, and there's also an infrared LED light I removed from a Raspberry Pi camera.
The plastic box has an odd shape because the nest box's side panels can rotate. I bought it like that, and it couldn't be modified, so I had to design it based on that.
Since there's no power supply in the garden, the entire setup is powered by a solar panel and a 2600 mAh 18650 lithium battery.
